k)\n* [[Tate and Liza|Liza]] (flashback)\n* [[Tate and Liza|Tate]] (flashback)\n* [[Juan]] (flashback)\n* [[Drew]] (flashback)\n* {{ho|Robert}} (flashback)\n* {{ho|Grace}} (flashback)\n* {{ho|Kelly}} (flashback)\n* [[Kent]] (flashback)\n* [[Harley]] (flashback)\n* [[Erica]] (flashback)\n* {{ho|Shauna}} (flashback)\n* {{ho|Kenny}} (flashback)\n* {{ho|Sebastian}} (flashback)\n\n===Pokémon===\n* {{p|Pikachu}} ({{OP|Ash|Pikachu}})\n* {{p|Swellow}} ({{OP|Ash|Swellow}})\n* {{p|Grovyle}} ({{OP|Ash|Grovyle}})\n* {{p|Corphish}} ({{OP|Ash|Corphish}})\n* {{p|Torkoal}} ({{OP|Ash|Torkoal}})\n* {{p|Snorunt}} ({{OP|Ash|Snorunt}})\n* {{p|Combusken}} ({{OP|May|Combusken}})\n* {{p|Beautifly}} ({{OP|May|Beautifly}})\n* {{p|Skitty}} ({{OP|May|Skitty}})\n* {{p|Bulbasaur}} ({{OP|May|Bulbasaur}})\n* {{p|Nosepass}} ({{OP|Roxanne|Nosepass}}; flashback)\n* {{p|Hariyama}} ({{OP|Brawly|Hariyama}}; flashback)\n* {{p|Slakoth}} ([[Norman]]'s; flashback)\n* {{p|Vigoroth}} ([[Norman]]'s; flashback)\n* {{p|Slaking}} ({{OP|Norman|Slaking}}; flashback)\n* {{p|Lunatone}} ({{OP|Liza|Lunatone}}; flashback)\n* {{p|Seaking}} ([[Juan]]'s; flashback)\n* {{p|Luvdisc}} ([[Juan]]'s; flashback)\n* {{p|Whiscash}} ([[Juan]]'s; flashback)\n* {{p|Milotic}} ([[Juan]]'s; flashback)\n* {{p|Roselia}} ({{OP|Drew|Roselia}}; flashback)\n* {{p|Medicham}} ({{ho|Grace}}'s; flashback)\n* {{p|Grumpig}} ({{ho|Kelly}}'s; flashback)\n* {{p|Cacturne}} ({{OP|Harley|Cacturne}}; flashback)\n* {{p|Jynx}} ([[Erica]]'s; flashback)\n* {{p|Lairon}} ([[Savannah]]'s; flashback)\n* {{p|Surskit}} ([[Kent]]'s; flashback)\n\n==Trivia==\n* This is the first episode since [[EP001|the very first one]] that [[Jessie]], [[James]], and {{MTR}} did not appear in, and the only one during the {{series|Advanced Generation}}.\n* The clip show had unedited audio playing with the scenes that utilized clips from prior episodes, similar to the Japanese version of ''[[Mewtwo Returns]]''.\n\n===Dub edits===\n* This episode was not dubbed into English, or any other language aside from the original Japanese. This occurred for the first time after the [[Banned episodes|worldwide-banned episode]] [[EP038]]. [[DP048]] and [[DP120]], both also clip shows, were skipped in the dub as well.\n\n==In other languages==\nAs most non-Japanese versions of the anime are based on the American dub, this episode has not aired anywhere outside of Japan.\n\n{{-}}\n{{EpicodePrevNext|\nprevcode=AG119 |\nprevtitle=The Ribbon Cup Caper |\nnextcode=AG121 |\nnexttitle=Hi Ho Silver Wind! |\nseries=Advanced Generation series |\ncolorscheme=Hoenn}}\n{{Project Anime notice}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:0394}}\n[[Category:Advanced Generation series episodes|120]]\n[[Category:Episodes with Gym battles]]\n[[Category:Episodes with Contests]]\n[[Category:Episodes focusing on Ash]]\n[[Category:Episodes focusing on May]]\n[[Category:Clip episodes]]\n[[Category:Undubbed episodes]]\n\n[[de:Satoshi to Haruka! Hōen de no Atsuki Battle!!]]\n[[es:EP397]]\n[[fr:AG120]]\n[[ja:AG編第120話]]\n[[zh:精灵宝可梦 超世代 总集篇]]"}